    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>, <date>October 8,
                1866</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very honored Sir: I transmit $50 to<lb/> you. Let me know whether
                you have received it.<lb/> I have not yet sold the Pentateuchs with English<lb/>
                translation, either in the ordinary or fine<lb/> binding, but I have orders from six
                men for<lb/> the same expensive Bibles as well as English<lb/> prayer books. I need
                Bibles that are bound like<lb/> the last ones I received, and prayer books for<lb/>
                women by <persName>Heather Rothschild</persName>, reprinted by you, well-<lb/>bound
                and with gilted locks. The former locks were very<lb/> poor. I had to sell them at a
                50 cent loss.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please write to me by return mail the<lb/> price for medium and
                ordinary well-bound<lb/> Bibles in English, the so-called parlor-Bible
                <add>?</add>.<lb/> I want to see, then, whether I could sell a<lb/> dozen. Write to
                me the price for freight if I<lb/> should have to pay it and still earn some-<lb/>
                thing. That means three different prices.<lb/> The women's prayer books in English
                must be<lb/> very nicely bound with gilt locks. Please let<lb/> me know the price,
                then I shall give you the<lb/> order.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If Hebrew Bibles cannot be sold, the<lb/> Jews should buy English
                ones. “That it<lb/> should not be forgotten among his seed.”<lb/> I am looking for
                your immediate response. I<lb/> still feel weak after my sickness. The hand
                still<lb/> trembles. My congregation gave me a gift of $300<lb/> for <date>Rosh
                    Hashonah</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">H. Kuttner</persName>
            </p>
            <p>The city number has been changed. My<lb/> address is <persName role="author">Rev. H.
                    Kuttner</persName>. <placeName>Box No 804,North 10th St. Between Mason<lb/> and
                    Franklin Avenue</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
